Here is a possible implementation in Julia:

```julia
abstract type AbstractVehicle end

struct Car <: AbstractVehicle end;
struct Motorcycle <: AbstractVehicle end;
struct Bus <: AbstractVehicle end;
struct Truck <: AbstractVehicle end;

function ispersonal(::Car)     return true end; 
function ispersonal(::Motorcycle)   return true end;
function ispersonal(::Bus)      return false end; 
function ispersonal(::Truck)    return false end; 

# default to false for any other subtype of AbstractVehicle
ispersonal(v::AbstractVehicle) = false;
```

You can test the function with an example:

```julia
println(ispersonal(Car()))      # prints true
println(ispersonal(Motorcycle()))  # prints true
println(ispersonal(Bus()))    # prints false
println(ispersonal(Truck()))   # prints false
println(ispersonal(AbstractVehicle())) # prints false
```
